1
00:00:00,940 --> 00:00:02,010
(Episode 35)

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:04,340
- Oh, really?
- I'm telling you, he did.

3
00:00:04,340 --> 00:00:05,610
My goodness.

4
00:00:06,780 --> 00:00:08,610
- I wonder who's here.
- To think of running into you here.

5
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:13,690
Oh, my, so it's true?
Baek Ho really helped you?

6
00:00:15,590 --> 00:00:18,720
I never knew Baek Ho
had such a romantic side.

7
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:23,630
Mother, wasn't our Baek Ho
always a romantic at heart?

8
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:24,900
"Mother?"

9
00:00:25,330 --> 00:00:26,800
"Our Baek Ho?"

10
00:00:27,270 --> 00:00:29,100
- Who is she?
- Or...

11
00:00:29,830 --> 00:00:32,000
maybe he's only romantic with me?

12
00:00:32,270 --> 00:00:35,640
Oh, my.

13
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:37,280
Oh, my.

14
00:00:37,810 --> 00:00:39,740
- So, what is it?
- Goodness.

15
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,110
This young lady is quite the charmer.

16
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,280
Right, Mother?

17
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:47,520
You should stop.
What are you doing with me sitting here?

18
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:50,590
You're the one who should stop.

19
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:54,260
Of all the women out there,
you had to pick a side dish shop owner?

20
00:00:54,930 --> 00:00:56,690
I went to her place,
and their circumstances are pathetic.

21
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,300
- And her mother isn't all there, either.
- Wait, Mom, you went to Jang Mi's place?

22
00:01:02,070 --> 00:01:03,170
Mom, I can't believe you...

23
00:01:10,540 --> 00:01:11,540
Jang Mi.

24
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:21,050
Of all the times for that Jang Mi girl
to show up.

25
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:30,060
Jang Mi!

26
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:33,970
I'm sorry.

27
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:36,670
You have nothing to be sorry for.

28
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,070
Everything your mother said is true.

29
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:42,270
Our family's situation...

30
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:45,480
- and my mom whom I have to take care of.
- I'm so sorry.

31
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:49,210
I'll apologize a thousand times
for my mom.

32
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,980
No, you don't have to apologize.

33
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:54,790
Go ahead and ask anyone on the street.

34
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:57,460
A respectable lawyer
from a top university,

35
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:02,230
dating an ordinary woman with no degree,
running a side dish shop for her sick mom,

36
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:03,290
and see what they say.

37
00:02:03,330 --> 00:02:05,560
What are you talking about?
You're not an ordinary woman.

38
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:07,870
To me, you're precious and special.

39
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:10,700
Please don't think that way.

40
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:14,210
- Please.
- I don't need your pity.

41
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:18,780
Don't be unfilial to your mother.
It's time to come to your senses, Baek Ho.

42
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:22,480
There are plenty of women better than me.
Go find one.

43
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:48,440
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

44
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:55,450
Hong Ju. Am I supposed to let
Chae Hwa Young humiliate me every day?

45
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,880
I'm telling you to go dig up some dirt
on Chae Hwa Young.

46
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,590
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

47
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:13,530
CEO Jin Hong Ju.

48
00:03:14,370 --> 00:03:15,430
No, that's not it.

49
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:19,000
If my mom marries the Chairman,
I'll become Ma Hong Ju.

50
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:20,310
Then...

51
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:22,870
CEO Ma Hong Ju?

52
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:27,210
That's all. You can leave now.

53
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:34,190
Something's bound to turn up.

54
00:03:38,860 --> 00:03:40,760
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

55
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:51,600
What are you doing in here?

56
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:55,770
I was waiting for the CEO.

57
00:03:58,380 --> 00:03:59,710
Why were you going through her drawers...

58
00:04:00,450 --> 00:04:03,820
- when you were waiting for the CEO?
- Going through them? I was just...

59
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:08,450
Fine, I was looking for nail clippers.
I got bored waiting.

60
00:04:08,550 --> 00:04:09,920
Do you really expect me to believe that?

61
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:12,490
Believe it or not, it's the truth.

62
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,590
By the way, Manager Lee.

63
00:04:16,230 --> 00:04:19,160
You know the CEO better than anyone,
don't you?

64
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:24,770
There's a rumor going around the office
that the CEO is dating someone.

65
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:28,570
Manager Lee, you should keep a better eye
on the CEO.

66
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:30,710
Who starts rumors like that?

67
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:32,510
Whatever.

68
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:34,180
I think you should leave now.

69
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:36,310
I left the documents over there
for her approval.

70
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,720
Please give them to the CEO
when she arrives.

71
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:04,010
You went to the fish market at dawn,
bought fresh anchovies,

72
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,510
and fermented these from scratch.

73
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:07,510
Fermented anchovies are expensive
if you buy them from a market.

74
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,350
Saving money on ingredients is important,

75
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:14,150
but the taste is so much better
when you ferment them by hand.

76
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:19,560
As expected of you, Chef! You're the best!

77
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:21,690
Is everything ready
for tonight's dinner service?

78
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:24,400
It's handmade spaghetti...

79
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:27,170
- with fresh anchovies.
- Yes, Chef!

80
00:05:30,170 --> 00:05:31,170
Hello, CEO.

81
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:36,170
Mr. Park. Yes.

82
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:56,060
Jun Ho.

83
00:05:57,060 --> 00:06:00,700
Thank you for growing up so well,
even without your mom.

84
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:02,970
My son, Ha Neul.

85
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:06,200
Now, I'm going to give you everything.

86
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,770
Now, I can give you everything.

87
00:06:23,290 --> 00:06:27,990
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

88
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:35,530
To make my Jun Ho the successor
to Dream Group,

89
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:39,400
I'll need to give him a position
on par with Seo Rin's.

90
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:44,810
Manager Lee, come in.

91
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:50,720
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

92
00:06:50,850 --> 00:06:52,850
- Hey, Jang Mi.
- Hi.

93
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:01,930
- Hey, who are you?
- Dad!

94
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:03,590
- Stop right there!
- Dad!

95
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:04,660
Hey, you punk!

96
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:08,500
- What's going on?
- Tae Pyung. Quick, go after Dad.

97
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,300
- Dad!
- Hey!

98
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,640
- Dad!
- Hey!

99
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:16,970
What? Hong Ju went through my office?

100
00:07:17,410 --> 00:07:19,340
- Yes.
- Has she lost her mind?

101
00:07:19,910 --> 00:07:22,110
But what was she looking for?

102
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:24,520
It didn't look like
she knew about Oh Jang Mi.

103
00:07:24,820 --> 00:07:25,950
How can you be so sure?

104
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:27,450
She claimed the employees...

105
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:30,890
are gossiping about your love life...

106
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:34,290
and was just fishing
for who you're dating.

107
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:38,500
- That wasn't your real question?
- People are watching.

108
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:41,330
How long do you think Chairman Ma
will turn a blind eye?

109
00:07:41,470 --> 00:07:44,000
I'll handle that. Don't overstep.

110
00:07:46,970 --> 00:07:49,470
I've been by your side for over 30 years.

111
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:51,640
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

112
00:07:51,710 --> 00:07:53,480
It feels like you don't trust me,

113
00:07:55,410 --> 00:07:56,450
and it hurts.

114
00:07:58,550 --> 00:07:59,820
It's not like that.

115
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:04,060
Kang Hyuk, what's gotten into you lately?

116
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:06,720
I'm having a hard enough time as it is.

117
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:18,440
I'm going to end things
with Professor Kang soon.

118
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:20,740
Don't worry.

119
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,880
Hwa Young.

120
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:34,550
You know I'm always...

121
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,120
in your corner too, right?

122
00:08:43,330 --> 00:08:44,400
About Kang Jun Ho.

123
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:47,100
I'm going to promote him
to General Manager.

124
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,500
What?

125
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,070
Kang Jun Ho?

126
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:51,340
Yes.

127
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,840
When you think about it,
he's exceptionally talented.

128
00:08:54,610 --> 00:08:56,540
I used to think he was arrogant,

129
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:00,310
but he was just confident in his skills
and didn't bow to anyone.

130
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:02,710
You know how it is.

131
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:05,280
When you know you're good,
you don't have to bow to anyone.

132
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,650
He just had faith in his own talent.

133
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,860
We can't let talent like that go to waste,
can we?

134
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:12,990
You.

135
00:09:13,930 --> 00:09:15,260
Is there something between you
and Kang Jun Ho?

136
00:09:15,430 --> 00:09:17,500
Have you not been listening
to a word I've said?

137
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:21,670
- Didn't you hear? Promote him.
- Tell me.

138
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,730
What is it you're hiding from me?

139
00:09:30,610 --> 00:09:31,610
What?

140
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:35,010
- An assailant went after Jang Mi again?
- That's what I'm saying.

141
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:38,420
My dad chased after him, but he got away.

142
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:40,220
Things were quiet for a while.
We can't let this go on.

143
00:09:40,590 --> 00:09:43,650
I'm going to the police station right now
to request protection for Jang Mi.

144
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,720
Police protection?

145
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,490
Of course we should.

146
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:48,430
Forget it. I can protect myself.

147
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:50,630
Don't tell Baek Ho about this, Tae Pyung.

148
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:51,830
Okay, got it.

149
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,370
Too late. I told him everything.

150
00:09:57,230 --> 00:10:00,600
Darn it, it was so close.
If I were just a bit younger,

151
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:03,210
I would've chased that punk down,
grabbed him by the collar,

152
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:07,080
- and slammed him to the ground.
- You could've gotten hurt doing that.

153
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:10,780
Promise me you won't do that again, okay?

154
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:12,380
Anyway, this is all so weird.

155
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:15,320
- Why is someone targeting Jang Mi?
- Tell me about it.

156
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:30,130
I've got to dig up dirt on Chae Hwa Young,
and fast.

157
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:40,780
Why are you choking on your food
like that?

158
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:43,580
Here, drink some water, okay?

159
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,720
- Here you go.
- Okay.

160
00:10:49,620 --> 00:10:52,790
Well, our Seo Rin seems to be
in a great mood today.

161
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:56,360
Of course I am.
There's no reason not to be, Grandpa.

162
00:10:57,190 --> 00:10:58,700
That's my girl.

163
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:02,930
Hey! Get me some food.

164
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,370
Starting tomorrow, I'm having breakfast
before going to work.

165
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:07,200
I have to start working hard.

166
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:09,710
But you said you were only eating salads
starting today.

167
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:13,140
Whatever. Bring it when I say so.
You talk too much.

168
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,250
Sure.

169
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:17,980
There's no keeping up with her.

170
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:23,590
San Wol. After we eat,
I'm going to inspect your housework.

171
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:36,000
You're setting me up for the Chairman,
aren't you?

172
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:41,210
This makes
the Chairman look bad too, you know.

173
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:44,780
Really? If it makes Father look so bad,

174
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,380
why do you think he just stood by
and watched it happen?

175
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:50,410
Well...

176
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:53,150
It means you're nothing to him.

177
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,820
No matter how much I mess with you,

178
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:59,920
- it's proof you mean nothing to Father.
- What?

179
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:02,890
Why do you think I put you on the spot
in front of Father?

180
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,160
Don't you get it?

181
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,000
I was testing...

182
00:12:07,730 --> 00:12:10,530
to see how important you were to Father.

183
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:13,870
Turns out, you're nothing to him.

184
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:24,750
So, I went to that side dish shop.

185
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:26,350
My gosh.

186
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:29,390
Putting aside the fact that her family
is struggling,

187
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:31,790
her mother isn't all there.

188
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:36,190
- Gosh, it was a total madhouse.
- It was?

189
00:12:36,590 --> 00:12:40,130
So that's the family of the girl
Baek Ho is so crazy about?

190
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:41,470
That's what I'm saying.

191
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:44,940
This is a serious problem, honey.

192
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,170
That kid, honestly.

193
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:51,280
But as luck would have it,
I think I threw a wrench in their plans.

194
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:54,580
There's another young woman
who likes our Baek Ho,

195
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:57,720
and I was badmouthing that shop
in front of her.

196
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,720
And right at that moment,

197
00:13:00,050 --> 00:13:02,750
that Oh Jang Mi girl came
and heard the whole thing.

198
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:04,260
Really? And what happened?

199
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:05,420
I am so disappointed in you.

200
00:13:08,190 --> 00:13:12,000
Mom, I always thought you were fair
and without any prejudices.

201
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:14,300
That's why I respected
and looked up to you,

202
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:17,500
How could you go to Jang Mi's home
and then come back and slander her family?

203
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:20,370
Son, people will even badmouth the king
behind his back.

204
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:24,110
How was I supposed to know
that Oh Jang Mi girl was going to show up?

205
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:26,310
Do you have any idea how hurt she must be?

206
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:30,410
Anyway, no matter what anyone says,
I'm not giving up on Jang Mi.

207
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,150
So don't waste your energy,
trying to stop me.

208
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:34,920
Fine. We get it.

209
00:13:35,450 --> 00:13:37,920
We'll let you be for now,
since the more we stop you,

210
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,160
the more desperate you'll get.

211
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,830
But love doesn't work
the way you want it to.

212
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,730
Love is something you're drawn to
without realizing it,

213
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:47,670
like a swamp you can't escape from.

214
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:49,430
What was that?

215
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:54,240
Honey, you're talking
as if you're the one who's in love.

216
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:56,370
Goodness.

217
00:13:56,940 --> 00:13:57,940
In any case,

218
00:13:58,210 --> 00:14:01,110
I forbid you from seeing
that Oh Jang Mi woman.

219
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,650
Do you understand me?

220
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:10,920
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

221
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:16,660
Baek Ho is worried because weird things
have been happening around Jang Mi.

222
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:19,030
That's why he went to request
police protection for her.

223
00:14:19,530 --> 00:14:22,070
If I ever get my hands on that Ssangkal,
I won't let him be.

224
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:23,470
That rotten jerk.

225
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,800
Come on, Dad.
Just make sure you don't get hurt.

226
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:28,010
How are you supposed to fight
a monster like that?

227
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:30,170
By the way,

228
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:33,810
- do you have CEO Chae's phone number?
- The CEO? Why?

229
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:38,080
What do you mean, "why?"
She hasn't been in for side dishes lately.

230
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:41,320
I was just going to call and check on her
for customer service.

231
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,690
She's a valued customer.

232
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,090
- Found it.
- Wait.

233
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:06,110
- Hello?
- Oh, hello.

234
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:09,710
This is Oh Bok Gil, Oh Tae Pyung's father.

235
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:11,520
I'm not sure if you remember me.

236
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:14,250
- Yes, I do.
- Ma'am,

237
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:17,120
I know this is shameless of me to ask,
and I'm very sorry,

238
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:20,590
but would you be
Jang Mi's official sponsor?

239
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:22,290
I will cover all the costs.

240
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:27,430
If I say I'm sending her,
Jang Mi will absolutely pitch a fit,

241
00:15:27,930 --> 00:15:30,170
and she'll absolutely refuse to go.

242
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:34,740
I offered to send her before,
but she already turned me down.

243
00:15:34,870 --> 00:15:36,140
Yes, I know.

244
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:38,780
But Jang Mi almost died.

245
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,440
Not just once, but several times.

246
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,780
She went to the police station
to ask for police protection,

247
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:45,680
but I can't bear the anxiety.

248
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,020
So my first priority is
to send her to study abroad.

249
00:15:49,090 --> 00:15:52,290
This isn't a good time for me to talk.
I'll call you back.

250
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:59,160
On second thought, I'll come to you.
Let's talk in person.

251
00:15:59,230 --> 00:16:01,170
Okay, thank you so much.

252
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:04,070
All right, I'll wait for your call then.

253
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:12,310
That'll be all. You may go.
And did you tell Chef Kang to come see me?

254
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:13,580
Yes, ma'am.

255
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:25,220
Now, of all times, he's asking me
to send Oh Jang Mi abroad?

256
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:28,490
What's the better move here?

257
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,260
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

258
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:37,370
Should I head to the hotel?

259
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,900
I have to drop off the side dishes anyway.

260
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:42,870
Right.

261
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:47,140
I can't make someone so important
come all the way out here.

262
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:48,850
I should go to her.

263
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:53,550
Tae Sook, watch the store for me.
I have to step out for a bit.

264
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:56,190
- Where to?
- To meet someone.

265
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,020
Who are you meeting?

266
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:00,290
Where's he off to in such a rush?

267
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,730
(Bus Stop)

268
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:22,810
I can't believe he's making me,
Chae Hwa Young, of all people, this giddy.

269
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:25,980
This must be what it feels like
to be a mother for the first time.

270
00:17:26,980 --> 00:17:28,690
A mother, waiting for her son.

271
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:32,660
Come in.

272
00:17:40,630 --> 00:17:43,430
Welcome, Chef Kang. Have a seat.

273
00:17:53,910 --> 00:17:55,280
What is this about?

274
00:17:55,850 --> 00:17:57,050
It seems like...

275
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:59,620
eating with me
has become your new favorite hobby.

276
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:01,050
Let's eat first.

277
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:04,090
It's well past lunch. You must be hungry.

278
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:06,560
I always eat lunch late.

279
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:09,030
When we're busy with the rush,

280
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:12,030
- I often end up skipping it.
- Is that so?

281
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:13,730
I had no idea.

282
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:16,300
That must be tough.

283
00:18:17,030 --> 00:18:18,970
That's precisely why I called you here.

284
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:29,080
Go on, eat. Consider it part of the job.

285
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:31,150
You told me to keep in mind
that Japanese tour groups...

286
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:32,380
will be visiting next month.

287
00:18:32,380 --> 00:18:36,690
- Is this your way of demanding it?
- Bingo. So, eat up.

288
00:18:52,570 --> 00:18:54,940
Stop crying.

289
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,840
What can I do?
We don't have any money, sweetie.

290
00:18:58,810 --> 00:19:01,450
We don't even have money for formula.

291
00:19:09,990 --> 00:19:13,620
That old saying, "A parent's belly is full
just watching their child eat,"

292
00:19:14,490 --> 00:19:15,990
wasn't an exaggeration, after all.

293
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:19,330
And to think I'm only realizing it now.

294
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:22,100
Thank you,

295
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:23,730
Jun Ho.

296
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:28,770
I saw that you double-majored in business.

297
00:19:29,340 --> 00:19:31,070
May I ask why?

298
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:35,710
Every chef dreams of opening
their own restaurant one day.

299
00:19:36,810 --> 00:19:38,480
You need business acumen to do that.

300
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:40,950
Dream Hotel needs to revamp its image.

301
00:19:41,620 --> 00:19:45,160
As I said at the grand reopening,
we're aiming for innovation,

302
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:48,430
but the reality is, that's impossible
without the right talent.

303
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,060
What are you getting at?

304
00:19:52,530 --> 00:19:55,770
Wining and dining me
just to blindside me won't work on me.

305
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:01,470
I plan to recommend you, Chef Kang Jun Ho,
who is young and competent,

306
00:20:02,010 --> 00:20:04,470
for the General Manager position.

307
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:06,810
Me?

308
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:09,510
As General Manager?

309
00:20:18,460 --> 00:20:22,590
The person you're calling is unavailable.
Connecting to voicemail.

310
00:20:22,660 --> 00:20:24,930
You will be charged for this call
after the tone.

311
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:29,500
Hwa Young, please, let's meet.
Let's talk this over in person.

312
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:32,640
We can't just end things like this.
It's insane.

313
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:39,580
I'll be home all day as I have no class.
Please call me. I'll be waiting.

314
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:51,990
What's your angle this time?

315
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,330
Looks like you've finally decided
to change up your strategy.

316
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:57,490
Chef Kang, you're crossing a line.

317
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:00,100
I am the CEO of Dream Hotel.

318
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:04,030
And I don't intend to play games
with one of my employees.

319
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,800
Just give me your answer to my offer.

320
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:10,210
Actually, don't bother answering.

321
00:21:11,170 --> 00:21:14,240
I'm appointing you as General Manager,
and that's final.

322
00:21:16,910 --> 00:21:17,910
I refuse.

323
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:19,820
What?

324
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:27,620
What?
You got caught searching Hwa Young's desk?

325
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:31,630
Well, you're the one who told me
to dig up some dirt on CEO Chae.

326
00:21:31,930 --> 00:21:33,830
And all it got me was getting caught
by Manager Lee.

327
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:36,900
Gosh, what am I going to do?
I'm scared of what might happen afterward.

328
00:21:41,140 --> 00:21:42,310
This is a disaster.

329
00:21:42,940 --> 00:21:44,270
That witch, Hwa Young,

330
00:21:44,510 --> 00:21:47,540
must know that
Hong Ju went through her desk.

331
00:21:48,050 --> 00:21:49,910
I can't imagine
how she'll chew me out later.

332
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:58,320
I wouldn't care
if it was just me suffering,

333
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:00,320
but for my Hong Ju to go through this...

334
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,230
Mrs. Yeom.

335
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:08,330
- What's on your mind? Why the long sigh?
- Chairman.

336
00:22:10,930 --> 00:22:13,740
Hey, there. Goodness. Hey.

337
00:22:18,010 --> 00:22:19,480
- Hey, Mrs. Yang.
- Yes?

338
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:21,910
Get some water. Quickly.

339
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:25,020
Hey, Mrs. Yeom, stay with me!

340
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:27,650
Goodness, look at all this sweat.

341
00:22:28,090 --> 00:22:30,950
I'd better call Dr. Kim.

342
00:22:31,860 --> 00:22:34,320
What? Dr. Kim? No.

343
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,160
Here, drink some water. Okay?

344
00:22:39,330 --> 00:22:42,700
There you go. Yes, that's it. Good.

345
00:22:42,770 --> 00:22:44,800
That's it.

346
00:22:45,570 --> 00:22:46,600
Good.

347
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:49,540
Chairman.

348
00:22:49,810 --> 00:22:51,310
Yes, it's me.

349
00:22:52,010 --> 00:22:53,440
Are you feeling a little better now?

350
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:56,580
Chairman.

351
00:23:00,180 --> 00:23:03,150
I can't live like this anymore.
It's too much.

352
00:23:03,690 --> 00:23:06,160
I know. I'm sorry.

353
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:11,460
I'm so sorry I just stood by
and let you suffer, Mrs. Yeom.

354
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:13,160
Now, don't cry.

355
00:23:13,830 --> 00:23:16,000
- Stop crying.
- Chairman.

356
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:20,100
Honestly, that's enough now, okay?

357
00:23:22,070 --> 00:23:23,970
What's the reason
for doing this all of a sudden?

358
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:26,440
Are you promoting me,
a thorn in your side,

359
00:23:27,410 --> 00:23:29,880
to General Manager all of a sudden,

360
00:23:30,810 --> 00:23:32,780
just so you can set me up
on an important project...

361
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:36,220
and throw me in prison this time?

362
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:41,160
You've really got me all wrong.

363
00:23:45,730 --> 00:23:46,900
I'm sorry.

364
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:51,130
It's my fault you misunderstood me
to this extent, Chef Kang.

365
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:52,500
I'm truly sorry.

366
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:57,870
I'm really sorry for abusing my power
and giving you such a hard time.

367
00:23:58,740 --> 00:24:01,340
So please, accept my offer.

368
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:05,120
I'll make the appointment official soon,
so be ready.

369
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:08,420
Since you're putting it that way...

370
00:24:11,290 --> 00:24:12,290
All right.

371
00:24:14,590 --> 00:24:15,590
Very well.

372
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,400
The General Manager
of the Dream's Kitchen...

373
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,230
I'll do it. However,

374
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:25,200
I have a condition.

375
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:26,740
A condition?

376
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:35,050
That's enough, Chairman.

377
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:38,780
Tomorrow, you need to go to the hospital
for a check-up.

378
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:43,490
Or should I ask CEO Chae
to get you some restorative tonics?

379
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,460
Chairman.

380
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:50,460
Can't you see how CEO Chae
has been treating me?

381
00:24:50,890 --> 00:24:55,730
Do you really have no idea
why I collapsed today?

382
00:24:55,830 --> 00:24:59,840
Of course I know. It's because you caused
a needless misunderstanding,

383
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:03,010
and that's why someone as reasonable
as CEO Chae got upset.

384
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:08,040
I'm telling you, she's seeing a man.

385
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:10,950
Chairman! Just think about it.

386
00:25:11,350 --> 00:25:14,450
Would a daughter-in-law
who's seeing another man...

387
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:18,860
admit it to her own father-in-law?

388
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,860
That's not who CEO Chae is.

389
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:26,430
You're wrong about her. For decades,
she has never looked at another man...

390
00:25:26,630 --> 00:25:30,300
and only worked to make Seo Rin the heir
to carry on the family line.

391
00:25:30,670 --> 00:25:34,070
Don't get worked up over nothing, okay?

392
00:25:35,710 --> 00:25:39,010
If you say so, Chairman,
I guess that's that.

393
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:45,320
But CEO Chae will take it out
on my Hong Ju.

394
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:48,390
Just yesterday, Hong Ju
went to get something approved,

395
00:25:48,850 --> 00:25:51,150
but CEO Chae wasn't there,
and she got bored waiting.

396
00:25:51,420 --> 00:25:53,860
So Hong Ju was looking
for some nail clippers,

397
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:57,660
and she rummaged through a desk drawer
for a moment. But then...

398
00:25:58,060 --> 00:25:59,300
Okay.

399
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:02,130
You think I don't understand how you feel?

400
00:26:03,130 --> 00:26:05,600
What good does that do?

401
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:09,470
I didn't come to this house
to be treated like a maid.

402
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:13,040
I came here because
I was devoted to you and you alone.

403
00:26:13,140 --> 00:26:15,910
Yet, my daughter and I
are being humiliated like this.

404
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:20,220
This is no way to live.

405
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:24,520
I don't know
when this nightmare will ever end.

406
00:26:30,860 --> 00:26:32,530
All right. What's your condition?

407
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:36,800
As long as you're not asking me
to keep you away from my Seo Rin,

408
00:26:37,070 --> 00:26:38,230
I'll agree to anything.

409
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:41,340
That's exactly what I'm asking.

410
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:45,110
I have no desire to work with a stalker.

411
00:26:49,210 --> 00:26:50,210
Gosh.

412
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:56,890
Goodness! What am I going to do?

413
00:26:57,050 --> 00:26:59,290
- Gosh.
- Shoot. I dropped it.

414
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:01,990
Who is this solicitor?

415
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:03,790
Wait.

416
00:27:04,130 --> 00:27:06,930
Jang Mi. What are you doing here?

417
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:11,170
Hey, if you're going to bump into me,
you could at least apologize.

418
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:14,370
Oh, you're not Jang Mi.

419
00:27:15,210 --> 00:27:16,270
I'm so sorry.

420
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:32,720
What? You're not Jang Mi.

421
00:27:33,390 --> 00:27:34,920
You're pretending to be Jang Mi.

422
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:37,130
- You're not Jang Mi.
- What's with this woman?

423
00:27:38,130 --> 00:27:39,130
Jang Mi?

424
00:27:42,530 --> 00:27:45,800
Hey! Who on earth is Jang Mi?

425
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:15,230
(The First Man)

426
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:18,740
Don't tell me Ssangkal's boss...

427
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:22,310
is Manager Lee,
the one who tried to hurt my Jang Mi.

428
00:28:22,670 --> 00:28:26,340
"Suk Hee's Side Dishes?"
The address is on here too.

429
00:28:26,410 --> 00:28:29,310
How much could this girl look like me
for them to mistake me for their daughter?

430
00:28:29,710 --> 00:28:31,080
You're asking if I've seen Oh Bok Gil?

431
00:28:31,310 --> 00:28:33,450
If he's figured everything out,
we're in big trouble.

432
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:35,290
Find him now!

433
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:37,990
Chae Hwa Young.
She was the one behind it all along.

434
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:40,720
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
